{"word":"G3694 - ὀπίσω - opísō - op-is'-o - After","slug":"G3694","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">ὀπίσω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>opísō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>op-is'-o"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>After"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03BF;&#x0313;&#x0301;&#x03C0;&#x03B9;&#x0301;&#x03C3;&#x03C9; - opiso&#x0304;</b> - <i>op-is'-o</i><p/>From the same as <a href=\"#/G3693\">G3693</a> with enclitic of direction; <i>to</i> the <i>back</i>, that is, <i>aback</i> (as adverb or preposition of time or place; or as noun): - after, back (-ward), (+ get) behind, + follow."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G3693\">G3693</a>"}]}